# Respond to each piece of feedback (CI and reviews)

Assistants (**Cursor**, **Codex**, **Claude / Claude Code**) must treat automated and human review signals as requiring **explicit closure**, not silent dismissal.

Works with **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`** and **`multiagent-modularity.mdc`** (watch checks; merge only when intended).

**Canonical phrase for merge readiness:** **enumerate threads → judge merits → reply in-thread** (implemented / deferred / declined), **then** squash-merge or enable auto-merge—see `.cursor/rules/git-pr-workflow-default.mdc` (“PR review bots”) so wording stays consistent across docs.

## What counts as feedback

- **Failures** from required workflows (tests, lint, **`ci_result`**, etc.).
- **Inline comments** and **reviews** from humans.
- **Bot / integration comments** such as **`sourcery-ai`** / **`gemini-code-assist`** / **`coderabbit`** / **`copilot`**, **`chatgpt-codex-connector`**, or similar on the opened PR—or **email / notification summaries** that map to findings on **the same branch the assistant owns**.

## Mandatory behaviour (each distinct finding)

1. **Enumerate** — distinct failing jobs, logs, review threads (merge truly duplicate verbatim threads into **one** reply that references both locations).
2. **Judge merits** against project rules and scope (**real-data-only tests**, **data-first UI**, modular files, scope of task). Prefer implementing good fixes; politely decline incorrect or out-of-scope items with a substantive reason—not silence.
3. **Respond directly** on GitHub (**preferred**):
   - **Accepted:** follow-up commits on the same branch **and/or** reply that the suggestion is addressed in commit `<sha>`.
   - **Declined or deferred:** reply on the thread with a concrete reason (out of scope, conflicts with **`AGENTS.md`**, backlog link, behavioural requirement, etc.).
4. Treat the branch as merge-ready **only after** substantive feedback threads are closed—not left hanging because a check stayed green while a bot commented.

## When GitHub inline replies are unavailable

Append **`## Feedback responses`** to the PR body—or the closing push summary—listing each item: source/tool (optional), file/topic, **done / skipped + why**, SHA if applicable.

## Do not

- Dismiss **`sourcery`**, **`gemini-code-assist`**, or similar as “non-blocking third-party noise” **without** per-item resolution (code + thread **or** written decline reason).
- Merge or finalize a PR the assistant owns when **identified** automated or human review comments remain unaddressed and unstated why.

## Relation to failing CI

- **Required failing checks**: fix-forward until green (existing **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**).
- **Bots that comment while checks succeed**: apply this document’s enumerate / judge / respond loop; passing CI **does not** waive thread closure.
